ENTRY            D6484   20250930   20260508   20260508       D151
SUBENT        D6484001   20250930   20260508   20260508       D151
BIB                 11         19
TITLE      Mass distributions in 12C+232Th fission: role of
            shell effects and excitation energy
AUTHOR     (S.Kumar, S.Patra, A.Mhatre, A.Kumar, K.Ramachandran,
            R.Tripathi)
INSTITUTE  (3INDTRM)
           (3INDIND) Homi Bhabha National Institute, Mumbai
REFERENCE  (J,EPJ/A,60,146,2024)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3INDTAT) Pelletron-LINAC facility
SAMPLE     Three self-supporting 232Th targets of thickness
            2.02, 1.88 and 1.95 mg/cm2. Each target was sandwiched
            between two Al catcher foils of thickness 6.75 mg/cm2.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Two coaxial detectors (~30% efficiency, 2 keV
            FWHM at 1332 keV) were used for gamma-ray spectrometry
METHOD     The samples were irradiated with at energies of 80.0,
            87.0, and 115.3 MeV for approximately 21.5, 17.0, and
            11.7 hours, respectively.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information on source of uncertainties.
STATUS     (TABLE,,S.Kumar+,J,EPJ/A,60,146,2024) Table 2
HISTORY    (20250930C) VT
ENDBIB              19
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           22
